237
00:11:26.750 --> 00:11:28.710
Oh, if you're hungry...

238
00:11:28.710 --> 00:11:31.000
You must be a holo-holo, too!

239
00:11:33.010 --> 00:11:35.170
What? I hit her! She's real?!

240
00:11:35.170 --> 00:11:39.140
Cut that "I hit her, she's real" crap!

241
00:11:39.140 --> 00:11:41.510
What are you doing, you jackass?!

242
00:11:41.510 --> 00:11:42.770
Sorry...

243
00:11:46.940 --> 00:11:48.060
Oh no!

244
00:11:48.060 --> 00:11:49.730
She's definitely real!

245
00:11:58.820 --> 00:11:59.530
What?

246
00:12:01.990 --> 00:12:02.700
What?

247
00:12:04.410 --> 00:12:05.120
What?

248
00:12:11.420 --> 00:12:14.300
This texture... This smell...

249
00:12:15.800 --> 00:12:18.720
A hamburger combo with fries and a drink!

250
00:12:18.720 --> 00:12:19.720
– Is it real?!
– Is it real?!

251
00:12:19.720 --> 00:12:21.220
Isn't it a holo-holo?!

252
00:12:21.220 --> 00:12:22.100
Can I touch it?

253
00:12:22.100 --> 00:12:22.970
Can I eat it?

254
00:12:26.810 --> 00:12:28.980
– Yummy!
– Yummy!

255
00:12:28.980 --> 00:12:30.980
It's really real!

256
00:12:32.560 --> 00:12:34.400
Wait... Who made it, though?!

257
00:12:34.400 --> 00:12:35.860
Wasn't it this thing?!

258
00:12:35.860 --> 00:12:37.150
It's not a person...

259
00:12:37.150 --> 00:12:39.410
...but when he pushed
a button, food came out.

260
00:12:39.410 --> 00:12:42.280
As long as we can get food,
who cares?! Push the next one!

261
00:12:42.280 --> 00:12:43.330
I'm on it!

262
00:12:43.330 --> 00:12:45.660
Steak! Rice omelet! Pork cutlet!

263
00:12:48.540 --> 00:12:51.000
– Yummy!
– Yummy!

264
00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:52.210
Next, next!

265
00:12:52.210 --> 00:12:53.380
Cotton candy cake!

266
00:12:53.380 --> 00:12:54.380
No, pizza!

267
00:12:54.380 --> 00:12:55.500
These ones first!

268
00:12:55.500 --> 00:12:57.630
Ramen, fried chicken, and a hot dog!

269
00:12:57.630 --> 00:13:00.720
Wait! If you push them all,
maybe they'll all come out at once!

270
00:13:00.720 --> 00:13:01.800
You're a genius!

271
00:13:01.800 --> 00:13:03.600
Good thinking, Chopper!

272
00:13:03.600 --> 00:13:05.970
Flattery will get you nowhere!

273
00:13:05.970 --> 00:13:07.270
Pick something, Jinbe!

274
00:13:07.270 --> 00:13:08.810
I'm fine, thank you.

275
00:13:13.230 --> 00:13:14.230
Yum!

276
00:13:14.230 --> 00:13:15.230
Yum!

277
00:13:15.230 --> 00:13:15.730
Yum!

278
00:13:15.730 --> 00:13:16.480
Yum!

279
00:13:16.480 --> 00:13:17.280
Yum!

280
00:13:17.650 --> 00:13:19.360
Wow, you sure do eat a lot.

281
00:13:19.360 --> 00:13:22.200
Well, duh! I was starving!

282
00:13:23.280 --> 00:13:25.620
Me, too!

283
00:13:24.280 --> 00:13:25.620
Me, too!

284
00:13:27.620 --> 00:13:28.370
Try this!

285
00:13:28.750 --> 00:13:30.750
I'm glad they like it.

286
00:13:30.750 --> 00:13:32.080
What's going on?

287
00:13:32.080 --> 00:13:33.330
What is that device?

288
00:13:33.330 --> 00:13:35.090
Curious, are you?

289
00:13:37.420 --> 00:13:39.800
It's my automated cooking machine!

290
00:13:39.800 --> 00:13:41.760
As long as there are ingredients,

291
00:13:41.760 --> 00:13:44.720
it can prepare any of its 
500 dishes in under a minute!

292
00:13:45.100 --> 00:13:48.680
The "whip up leftovers" mode
is particularly handy!

293
00:13:51.770 --> 00:13:54.860
If it were built according
to the blueprints, that is!

294
00:13:55.400 --> 00:13:58.360
But we lack the technicians
needed to mass-produce it!

295
00:13:58.360 --> 00:13:59.860
Same goes for the island A.C.

296
00:13:59.860 --> 00:14:02.490
If we could control
an entire island's temperature,

297
00:14:02.490 --> 00:14:05.740
then we could monitor
the biometrics of every organism!

298
00:14:05.740 --> 00:14:09.540
I've made such incredible inventions,

299
00:14:09.540 --> 00:14:13.420
but the situation isn't allowing
me to actualize their potential!

300
00:14:13.420 --> 00:14:18.090
If we had the money, 
we could even control the weather itself!

301
00:14:18.090 --> 00:14:20.840
The world lacks technology!
I need more funds!

302
00:14:20.840 --> 00:14:24.050
I'm working so hard to invent things,
so why is this happening?!

303
00:14:27.140 --> 00:14:28.760
Stop jerking me around!

304
00:14:30.220 --> 00:14:32.600
There aren't enough resources!

305
00:14:35.810 --> 00:14:38.020
She punched a hologram!

306
00:14:38.020 --> 00:14:39.270
Fried shrimp!

307
00:14:39.270 --> 00:14:40.980
Waffle!

308
00:14:45.360 --> 00:14:46.740
Ah, much better!

309
00:14:47.490 --> 00:14:48.950
How is that possible?

310
00:14:48.950 --> 00:14:51.910
How did you punch a hologram?

311
00:14:52.370 --> 00:14:54.790
Curious, are you? Allow me to explain.

312
00:14:54.790 --> 00:14:59.250
With these light-pressure gloves,
light is no longer something you just see.

313
00:15:01.590 --> 00:15:02.590
Hi!

314
00:15:03.720 --> 00:15:08.180
When you touch something,
you perceive it as a solid object, right?

315
00:15:08.180 --> 00:15:10.140
What? So she's not real?

316
00:15:10.140 --> 00:15:11.890
Not real?

317
00:15:14.100 --> 00:15:15.310
Luffy, look!

318
00:15:20.480 --> 00:15:22.360
Phew, so she wasn't real...

319
00:15:22.360 --> 00:15:24.990
I thought for sure she was...!

320
00:15:24.990 --> 00:15:28.240
Quit asking what's real and what's not!

321
00:15:28.240 --> 00:15:30.370
You decide for yourself!

322
00:15:30.370 --> 00:15:34.620
If you ask me, that concept
is just a relic of the past!

323
00:15:35.330 --> 00:15:36.080
So yummy!

324
00:15:36.080 --> 00:15:37.540
You aren't even listening!

325
00:15:37.540 --> 00:15:40.500
Just who in the world are you?

326
00:15:42.210 --> 00:15:43.260
Me?

327
00:15:43.760 --> 00:15:45.170
I'm just...

328
00:15:45.170 --> 00:15:47.430
a plain old genius scientist for hire,

329
00:15:51.640 --> 00:15:54.730
Dr. Vegapunk!

330
00:15:57.100 --> 00:15:58.900
<b>Atlas the Enraged</b>

331
00:15:59.480 --> 00:16:00.650
Yum!

332
00:16:02.940 --> 00:16:04.860
You're Dr. Vegapunk?!

333
00:16:04.860 --> 00:16:06.360
Koby told me all about you!

334
00:16:06.360 --> 00:16:08.610
You're so big! And so young!

335
00:16:08.610 --> 00:16:10.030
That's bull!

336
00:16:10.030 --> 00:16:11.950
What is she talking about?

337
00:16:11.950 --> 00:16:14.160
<b>New World</b>

338
00:16:17.120 --> 00:16:19.540
So, what's the plan?

339
00:16:20.290 --> 00:16:23.960
Listen. There's only one Vegapunk in the world,

340
00:16:23.960 --> 00:16:26.590
but because he's a genius,
he stays busy as a beaver.

341
00:16:27.090 --> 00:16:30.800
He's so strapped for time that
he'll take all the help he can get.

342
00:16:31.300 --> 00:16:33.510
Then it dawned on him...

343
00:16:33.890 --> 00:16:36.850
"What if I split myself into six bodies?"

344
00:16:36.850 --> 00:16:40.150
He calls those offshoots his satellites.

